gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 140, Wizards 115
gameRecap.excerpt: The Clippers defeated the Wizards, 140-115. James Harden led the way for the Clippers with 28 points (6-9 3pt. FG) and eight assists, while Kawhi Leonard (27 points, nine rebounds) and Paul George (22 points, six rebounds) added a combined 49 points in the victory. Kyle Kuzma notched a game-high 32 points (5-7 3pt. FG), along with seven rebounds for the Wizards in the losing effort. The Clippers improve to 38-20 on the season, while the Wizards fall to 9-51.
